        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 21 at 2:52PM CST by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 252 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Corrigan, or 10 miles south of Diboll, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Corrigan, Seven Oaks, and Moscow.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
